ISLAMABAD, Feb 1 (APP):Minister for Energy Hammad Azhar on Tuesday said that despite 9 per cent depletion in our supply from gas fields, the flow of gas to industry from Sui Southern Gas Company (SSGC) saw a reduction of only 3.54 per cent in Nov-Dec 21 compared to preceding year.
“Also, tariffs have multiplied globally yet most industry in SSGC have been insulated from any price rise since 2019,” he tweeted.
